#. <section class="sutta" id="sn47.21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.21:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.21:0.2"
msgid "3. Sīlaṭṭhitivagga"
msgstr "3. Ethics and Duration"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.21:0.3"
msgid "21. Sīlasutta"
msgstr "21. Ethics"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "sn47.21:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "sn47.21:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca ānando āyasmā ca bhaddo pāṭaliputte viharanti kukkuṭārāme."
msgstr "At one time the venerables Ānanda and Bhadda were staying at Pāṭaliputta, in the Chicken Monastery."

msgctxt "sn47.21:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā bhaddo sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Bhadda came out of retreat, went to Venerable Ānanda, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn47.21:1.4"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā bhaddo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to Ānanda:"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn47.21:1.5"
msgid "“yānimāni, āvuso ānanda, kusalāni sīlāni vuttāni bhagavatā, imāni kusalāni sīlāni kimatthiyāni vuttāni bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr "“Reverend Ānanda, the Buddha has spoken of skillful ethics. What’s their purpose?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.21:2.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, āvuso bhadda."
msgstr "“Good, good, Reverend Bhadda!"

#. VAR: ummaṅgo → ummaggo (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn47.21:2.2"
msgid "Bhaddako kho te, āvuso bhadda, ummaṅgo, bhaddakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ, kalyāṇī paripucchā."
msgstr "Your approach and articulation are excellent, and it’s a good question."

msgctxt "sn47.21:2.3"
msgid "Evañhi tvaṃ, āvuso bhadda, pucchasi:"
msgstr "For you asked:"

msgctxt "sn47.21:2.4"
msgid "‘yānimāni, āvuso ānanda, kusalāni sīlāni vuttāni bhagavatā, imāni kusalāni sīlāni kimatthiyāni vuttāni bhagavatā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘The Buddha has spoken of skillful ethics. What’s their purpose?’”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn47.21:2.5"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend.”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn47.21:2.6"
msgid "“Yānimāni, āvuso bhadda, kusalāni sīlāni vuttāni bhagavatā, imāni kusalāni sīlāni yāvadeva catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvanāya vuttāni bhagavatā."
msgstr "“The Buddha has spoken of skillful ethics to the extent necessary for developing the four kinds of mindfulness meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.172"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.21:3.1"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn47.21:3.2"
msgid "Idhāvuso, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.21:3.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "sn47.21:3.4"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn47.21:3.5"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.21:3.6"
msgid "Yānimāni, āvuso bhadda, kusalāni sīlāni vuttāni bhagavatā, imāni kusalāni sīlāni yāvadeva imesaṃ catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvanāya vuttāni bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr "The Buddha has spoken of skillful ethics to the extent necessary for developing the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.21:3.7"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
